{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, traffic scenes often involve various weather, lighting, and road conditions.",
    "Data augmentation can synthesize images under different conditions, including rainy, snowy, foggy, and strong light scenarios, to help the model adapt better to diverse environments.",
    "Reference [47]used a Data Anchor Sampling (DAS) method to increase training samples, particularly for smaller facial samples.",
    "This approach improved the accuracy and stability of the model.",
    "By appropriately selecting positive and negative samples and utilizing suitable loss functions, the target detection model could better understand the features and positions of target objects, thereby enhancing detection performance."
  ]
}